18:58.066 --> 19:00.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I know that.

19:00.166 --> 19:03.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we have got to begin the
discussion as to why we spend
so much more per capita on

19:03.633 --> 19:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
health care than any other
nation, why we pay the highest
prices in the world, why we

19:07.733 --> 19:11.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
do not guarantee health
care to all people, as every
other major country does.

19:11.433 --> 19:13.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, let me
ask you about what is going
to happen in the meantime.

19:13.866 --> 19:15.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You mentioned
prescription drug prices.

19:15.866 --> 19:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You mentioned having a
public option in different
parts of the country.

19:23.033 --> 19:25.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we know it's the case
that, in many states,
there is no insurance
company that is providing

19:28.033 --> 19:30.000 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
coverage.

19:30.000 --> 19:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Republicans like
to say the market, the
exchanges are collapsing.

19:33.166 --> 19:38.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What can be done in
the short term, Senator
Sanders, to shore these up?

19:38.100 --> 19:41.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Is there a way to come up
with subsidies that both
parties can agree to?

19:41.766 --> 19:42.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

19:42.766 --> 19:44.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
BERNIE SANDERS: Oh, yes.

19:44.000 --> 19:45.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Well, Judy, I think --
it's not me talking.

19:45.466 --> 19:47.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This is what the insurance
companies are saying.

19:47.966 --> 19:52.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What they're saying is,
there's great instability
in the marketplace,
precisely because of tweets

19:54.300 --> 19:58.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
like the one President -- the
president sent out today: Let's
see the Obamacare act destroyed.

19:59.966 --> 20:03.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, that's not exactly a
strong sign of confidence going
out to the insurance companies.

20:03.000 --> 20:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, what we have got to do
is, number one, we have to
enforce the individual mandate.

20:07.733 --> 20:10.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're losing a lot of money that
is not coming into the system.

20:10.533 --> 20:14.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, number two, we have
to deal with cost-sharing,
which is something we
have been doing many,

20:14.600 --> 20:16.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
many years.

20:16.633 --> 20:18.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you do that, I think
you will stabilize the
market for the short term.

20:18.966 --> 20:23.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But long term, longer term, we
have to improve the Affordable
Care Act, and longer term than

20:25.933 --> 20:28.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that we have to join the rest
of the world and guarantee
health care to all people as

20:28.100 --> 20:30.066 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a right.

20:30.066 --> 20:34.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: How much more
money is the federal government
going to have to put into

20:35.300 --> 20:36.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
health care in order
for this to work?

20:36.366 --> 20:37.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

20:37.833 --> 20:39.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BERNIE SANDERS: Well,
that's a very good question.

20:39.900 --> 20:43.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm sure that there's
absolutely nobody in the world
who knows the answer to it.

20:43.666 --> 20:48.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All that I can say is that
we are spending far more per
capita than people in any other

20:50.633 --> 20:54.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
country, and our health care
outcomes are in many cases worse
in terms of life expectancy,

20:55.533 --> 20:57.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
infant mortality and so forth.

20:57.666 --> 21:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I think the issue is
not necessarily -- we may
have to spend more money.

21:02.300 --> 21:07.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The issue is to trying to figure
out why we end up spending so
much more than other countries.

21:07.166 --> 21:10.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And one of the reasons, clearly,
high cost of prescription drugs.

21:10.833 --> 21:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Second reason, we do
very, very badly in terms
of primary health care.

21:14.800 --> 21:19.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are millions of people,
even those who have insurance,
who can not get to a doctor

21:19.500 --> 21:20.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
when they are sick.

21:20.933 --> 21:22.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They end up in the emergency
room, very expensive.

21:22.733 --> 21:25.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They end up in the hospital,
very, very expensive.

21:25.800 --> 21:30.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If we greatly expanded primary
health care, lower the cost
of prescription drugs, we take

21:30.266 --> 21:33.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a giant step forward in lowering
health care costs in America.

21:33.033 --> 21:37.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, very quickly,
if you had to name one area
where you could see an early

21:37.700 --> 21:41.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agreement between Democrats
and Republicans on health
care, what would it be?

21:41.400 --> 21:42.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:42.633 --> 21:44.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
BERNIE SANDERS:
Prescription drugs.

21:44.733 --> 21:46.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All right,
we are listening to you,
Senator Bernie Sanders.

21:46.266 --> 21:47.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

21:47.266 --> 21:48.266 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

21:48.266 --> 21:50.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
BERNIE SANDERS: Thank you, Judy.

21:50.433 --> 21:53.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, tomorrow
night, we are going to get a
Republican perspective, and

21:53.300 --> 21:58.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that will from Senator
Roger Wicker of Mississippi.

22:02.633 --> 22:07.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has been two years since the
Iran nuclear deal was struck,
a central and controversial

22:14.266 --> 22:17.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
part of the Obama
administration's legacy.

22:17.100 --> 22:21.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But President Trump has made
no secret of his dislike for
the agreement, and that is

22:21.533 --> 22:24.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
one part of heightened
tensions with Iran.

22:24.366 --> 22:26.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
William Brangham has more.

22:26.433 --> 22:29.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DONALD TRUMP, President of the
United States: My number one
priority is to dismantle the

22:29.733 --> 22:31.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
disastrous deal with Iran.

22:31.700 --> 22:34.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(CHEERING AND APPLAUSE)

22:34.400 --> 22:37.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: On the
campaign trail, candidate
Trump vowed to rip up the
international community's

22:37.900 --> 22:42.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agreement that curbed Iran's
nuclear program in exchange
for sanctions relief.

22:44.866 --> 22:47.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, last night, President
Trump took the required step
of certifying whether Iran was

22:49.133 --> 22:51.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in fact complying with
its end of the deal.

22:51.066 --> 22:56.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this was the second time
the Trump administration
certified it was.

22:58.033 --> 23:01.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
State Department spokeswoman
Heather Nauert, while affirming
Iran's compliance, said they're

23:01.133 --> 23:03.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
not off the hook.

23:03.166 --> 23:05.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HEATHER NAUERT, State Department
Spokeswoman: There are still
a lot of things Iran is doing

23:05.033 --> 23:07.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that are very troubling
to this administration.

23:07.466 --> 23:12.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so we're going to try and
push on the Iranian regime to
stop its destabilizing activity.

23:15.600 --> 23:19.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: In fact, the
president had to be convinced
by his national security team

23:19.900 --> 23:24.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Monday to agree to
this step, for now.

23:24.166 --> 23:29.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Simultaneously, the
administration maintained
a tough posture on Iran's
non-nuclear activities,

23:31.166 --> 23:35.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
imposing fresh sanctions on
its ballistic missile program
and its most elite military

23:35.900 --> 23:37.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
unit.

23:37.933 --> 23:41.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
U.S. officials say Iran's
ballistic missile tests, its
support for the militant group

23:41.200 --> 23:46.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Hezbollah, and its
increasing harassment of
other nations' ships in
the Persian Gulf violate

23:48.266 --> 23:50.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the spirit of the nuclear
agreement, though they're
not expressly prohibited.

23:50.733 --> 23:55.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HEATHER NAUERT: Some of the
actions the Iranian government
has been involved with undermine

23:57.633 --> 23:59.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that stated goal of
regional and international
peace and security.

23:59.666 --> 24:03.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Iranian
Foreign Minister Javad Zarif
insists Iran is living up to the

24:03.966 --> 24:08.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nuclear bargain and that the
U.S. has run afoul of the deal
by adding these new sanctions

24:08.800 --> 24:11.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and discouraging companies
from investing in Iran.

24:11.800 --> 24:15.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MOHAMMAD JAVAD ZARIF, Iranian
Foreign Minister: Iran, in our
view, and in the view of the

24:15.966 --> 24:20.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
IAEA, built trust
by implementing its
side of the bargain.

24:21.833 --> 24:23.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The United States didn't.

24:23.900 --> 24:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Zarif warned
that if this keeps up, Iran
could choose to pull out of

24:27.033 --> 24:29.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the deal itself.

24:29.633 --> 24:33.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, the U.S. says
it is reviewing its entire
Iran policy, even before
the next certification

24:34.800 --> 24:37.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
deadline, which is
just 90 days away.

24:37.533 --> 24:42.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For more on the future of the
Iranian nuclear deal, I'm joined
now by our own Margaret Warner

24:42.033 --> 24:43.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and Nick Schifrin.

24:43.033 --> 24:44.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Welcome to you both.

24:44.200 --> 24:46.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Nick, I want to
starts with you first.

24:46.200 --> 24:50.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I know you have been reporting,
and several others have, that
President Trump certifying

24:50.133 --> 24:54.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
that Iran was in fact
in compliance with the
deal was no easy matter.

24:54.666 --> 24:57.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Can you sort of explain,
what are the divisions
within the administration?

24:57.233 --> 24:59.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
NICK SCHIFRIN: Yes, this
was a real struggle.

24:59.633 --> 25:02.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
This time, we had what is
called the interagency process.

25:02.166 --> 25:06.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It took weeks to get to
the point where we were
about 12:00 yesterday.

25:06.033 --> 25:11.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that process said the
president is ready to recertify
that Iran is in compliance.

25:11.900 --> 25:14.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The president said not so fast.

25:14.433 --> 25:17.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On one side, you have
the president, President
Trump, and his chief
strategist, Steve Bannon.

25:17.466 --> 25:22.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a larger struggle,
frankly, vs. -- the pragmatic
vs. the ideological sides of the

25:24.800 --> 25:26.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
administration.

25:26.866 --> 25:28.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, you have Trump and Bannon
on one side, and you have
most of the national security

25:28.500 --> 25:31.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
establishment on the other side.

25:31.033 --> 25:34.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You have Secretary of
State Tillerson, Secretary
of Defense Mattis,
National Security Adviser

25:34.333 --> 25:36.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
H.R. McMaster, Joint Chiefs
Chairman Joe Dunford.

25:36.800 --> 25:41.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And for the next five
or six hours, those two
sides were debating.

25:41.166 --> 25:43.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The president and Bannon
say, we don't like the deal.

25:43.533 --> 25:44.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's not permanent.

25:44.933 --> 25:47.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And the deal is not
what Iran is about.

25:47.700 --> 25:52.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Iran is about the things that
your piece just mentioned,
ballistic weapons, not allowing

25:52.400 --> 25:57.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
free access in the Gulf,
terrorist support across
the region, and that's
the larger problem.

25:59.366 --> 26:03.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The other side said, look, you
may not like everything that
Iran does, but the fact is

26:05.900 --> 26:09.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that those other issues are
not part of the deal and that
Iran is in compliance, and,

26:10.500 --> 26:11.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
until it's not, you
have to recertify.

26:11.866 --> 26:14.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: So, Margaret,
help us out with that.

26:14.000 --> 26:17.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The argument is that if they're
not violating the letter of the
law, perhaps they're violating

26:17.400 --> 26:19.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the spirit of the law.

26:19.533 --> 26:21.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
What's true and what is not?

26:21.566 --> 26:23.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: It's true
that they are complying
with the letter of the law.

26:23.466 --> 26:26.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And the State Department
spokeswoman said it again today.

26:26.766 --> 26:29.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And there was no real
spirit of the law.

26:29.000 --> 26:34.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, there's a phrase about
it's hoped that everyone will
be positive in the region

26:34.600 --> 26:36.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
or something.

26:36.733 --> 26:40.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But the negotiators made
a deliberate decision
to corral, to only deal
with nuclear, because

26:42.300 --> 26:46.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
they knew if they got
into ballistic missiles
or Iran's threat on
Israel and all the other

26:46.733 --> 26:49.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
things you mentioned in
your piece, the whole
thing would fall apart.

26:49.733 --> 26:54.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There were some in
the administration who
had hoped that a more
benign environment would

26:56.766 --> 27:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
result because they built this
working relationship, John Kerry
and Javad Sharif, though a very

27:03.600 --> 27:06.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
senior official who did a lot
with Iran said to me, oh, me,
they are going to be actually

27:06.233 --> 27:10.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
worse after the deal because
they want to prove to the
hard-liners that they're not

27:10.766 --> 27:12.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
wimps and they're not weak.

27:12.766 --> 27:16.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The schism
that Nick is describing within
the Trump administration

27:16.433 --> 27:19.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is also reflected in a
schism within Iran itself.

27:19.766 --> 27:24.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Rouhani was
elected initially to
open up negotiations
with the West, to deliver

27:24.500 --> 27:26.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on this deal.

27:26.933 --> 27:30.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was recently reelected,
but that is not a
unanimous decision and
feeling within Iran.

27:31.366 --> 27:32.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MARGARET WARNER: No, it wasn't.

27:32.633 --> 27:34.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It wasn't certainly at the time.

27:34.733 --> 27:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He had to really -- Rouhani
and Supreme Leader Khamenei had
supported him, sort of, had to

27:41.166 --> 27:43.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
really fight hard-liners.

27:43.233 --> 27:47.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Where I do think there is a
lot of unhappiness in Tehran is
the point that Zarif made, that

27:49.733 --> 27:52.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the money has not rolled
in as they expected,
meaning foreign investment.

27:52.700 --> 27:56.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, part of it was, as
one person who had been very
involved said to me, oil was

27:56.833 --> 28:01.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
$100 a barrel when they started
the negotiations, $40 after.

28:01.133 --> 28:04.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The energy companies aren't
exactly dying to rush in.

28:04.500 --> 28:09.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Their banks are almost,
I wouldn't say insolvent,
but a lot of bad loans.

28:09.266 --> 28:14.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the companies have to
be big enough to come in
and fund it all themselves.

28:14.066 --> 28:18.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, finally, of course, there
are all these signals, and
they have gotten more intense

28:18.100 --> 28:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
since the Trump administration
came in, far from encouraging
banks -- or at least John

28:25.166 --> 28:28.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Kerry used to travel around
with groups of aides saying,
look, here is how you can do

28:28.566 --> 28:33.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
business, you won't run
afoul up the law -- the Trump
administration, that all ended.

28:33.566 --> 28:38.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, instead, you have Tillerson
saying things that -- and
Trump saying things that make

28:40.000 --> 28:42.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the Iranians nervous and
foreign investors nervous.

28:42.066 --> 28:44.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
