JEFFREY BROWN: All right, so
this case raises some -- plays
into some larger confusions

39:04.633 --> 39:06.666 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and that continuing controversy.

39:06.666 --> 39:10.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I want to ask you about one
other development in the visa
world that came yesterday.

39:10.600 --> 39:15.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The government announced they're
adding 15,000 new H-2B visas.

39:16.733 --> 39:17.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Now, explain what's
going on there.

39:17.833 --> 39:19.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
ALAN GOMEZ: Yes.

39:19.800 --> 39:22.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's just another example
of why it's so difficult to
try to figure out sort of

39:22.433 --> 39:26.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
what direction this
administration is going
when it comes to the
legal immigration system

39:26.433 --> 39:28.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in the United States.

39:28.500 --> 39:31.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just a couple of months ago,
to give you some background,
the president ordered a total

39:31.900 --> 39:35.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
review of the H-1B visa program.

39:35.400 --> 39:40.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Those are visas dedicated
to foreigners who are
trained in science,
technology, engineering,

39:40.066 --> 39:42.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
mathematics.

39:42.100 --> 39:44.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They're used by technology
companies to bring in computer
scientists and programmers.

39:44.966 --> 39:48.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the Trump administration
ordered a review of the program
because they believe that there

39:48.966 --> 39:53.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is too much fraud and that
these technology companies are
abusing that program to just

39:53.333 --> 39:54.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
import cheaper labor.

39:54.833 --> 39:56.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, we had that
as the background.

39:56.566 --> 39:58.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They talk about
American workers first.

39:58.433 --> 40:01.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And that's sort of the
posture that they have
been proceeding under.

40:01.066 --> 40:02.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: That's H-1.

40:02.066 --> 40:03.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's the H-1.

40:03.566 --> 40:05.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now, this is H-2, which
is for temporary workers.

40:05.433 --> 40:07.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ALAN GOMEZ: Right.

40:07.933 --> 40:10.466 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then, all of a sudden,
yesterday, we get this
announcement that they
are going to approve

40:10.466 --> 40:15.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
15,000 additional new
visas for H-2B visas, and
these are dedicated to
lower-skilled workers.

40:18.400 --> 40:23.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Think about people who work
in fisheries, in hotels, in
construction, in resorts, and

40:24.833 --> 40:26.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those are the kind of workers
that they're going to allow in.

40:26.900 --> 40:31.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The argument from the Trump
administration is that these
companies, a lot of them were

40:31.000 --> 40:34.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in very desperate need of
the labor, that they couldn't
find American workers to do

40:34.833 --> 40:37.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that job, so they needed to
bring in these additional
workers to do it.

40:37.800 --> 40:42.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, again, it sort of goes
against what the administration
has been arguing for all these

40:45.266 --> 40:47.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
months, that they are going
to limit the immigration
system to help American
workers and to reduce

40:49.333 --> 40:50.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the competition that they're
facing here in the country.

40:50.566 --> 40:52.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: All
right, ever evolving.

40:52.266 --> 40:55.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Alan Gomez, USA Today,
thanks very much.

40:55.666 --> 41:00.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ALAN GOMEZ: Thank you.

41:02.666 --> 41:07.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The United
Nations has called it the worst
humanitarian crisis since 1945,

41:12.033 --> 41:17.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and, just today, the lead
editorial in The Washington
Post called it the worst crisis

41:17.766 --> 41:19.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
you have never heard of.

41:19.833 --> 41:24.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Drought and famine threaten 20
million people in the war-torn
countries of Yemen, South

41:26.166 --> 41:30.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Sudan, and Somalia, as
well as drought-stricken
neighbors, such as Ethiopia.

41:30.266 --> 41:35.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This week, for the first
time, eight of the leading
U.S.-based international
relief organizations

41:36.633 --> 41:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are launching the Global
Emergency Response Coalition.

41:40.233 --> 41:45.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's a joint fund-raising appeal
to the American public due to
the hunger crisis, which will

41:46.466 --> 41:49.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
use social media to
amplify its message.

41:49.200 --> 41:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Special correspondent
Fred de Sam Lazaro
reports from the breakaway
region of Somalia known

41:54.833 --> 41:56.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as Somaliland.

41:56.933 --> 42:00.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: A glimpse
from our airplane window showed
the stark moonscape of drought

42:02.566 --> 42:06.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
stretching for miles on
end, where many regions
in East Africa are at
risk of famine for the

42:07.466 --> 42:11.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
third time in 25 years.

42:11.900 --> 42:16.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
More than 360,000 children
are malnourished in Somalia;
70,000 of them are in critical

42:18.333 --> 42:21.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
condition, according to the
World Health Organization.

42:21.133 --> 42:26.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We traveled to Somaliland,
a region that declared
itself independent of
Somalia more than two

42:26.733 --> 42:28.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
decades ago.

42:28.700 --> 42:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Its capital, Hargeisa, has seen
an influx of mostly nomadic
livestock herders fleeing

42:34.066 --> 42:37.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the drought and in some
cases fighting in the
vast surrounding region.

42:37.733 --> 42:40.766 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
They now live in
temporary camps.

42:40.766 --> 42:45.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Thirty-old-Year-old Hamda
Abdilahi Dhamac is the
mother of five children.

42:47.800 --> 42:50.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She came here after all of
her livestock, some 30 goats
and 50 sheep, died from the

42:51.366 --> 42:53.533 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
drought.

42:53.533 --> 42:55.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HAMDA ABDILAHI DHAMAC,
Somaliland (through
translator): I used
to be part of a family

42:55.066 --> 42:57.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of livestock herders.

42:57.166 --> 42:59.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But now I have been forced
to come to this camp, where I
don't have enough money to buy

42:59.700 --> 43:00.933 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
food and water.

43:00.933 --> 43:03.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I am really suffering.

43:03.000 --> 43:07.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: She gets
some money from relatives, but
says it's just enough to buy

43:08.366 --> 43:10.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
rice and perhaps
an onion or tomato.

43:10.866 --> 43:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She can't afford beans or meat.

43:14.400 --> 43:18.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like Dhamac, a majority
of Somalis make their
living by grazing animals.

43:18.966 --> 43:22.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But the drought has wiped out
70 percent of all livestock.

43:22.400 --> 43:25.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Dhamac says she doesn't know how
she will survive in the future.

43:25.733 --> 43:28.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
HAMDA ABDILAHI DHAMAC
(through translator): I
don't have any hope now.

43:28.966 --> 43:31.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't have a
plan for my future.

43:31.033 --> 43:36.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Humanitarian
organizations are distributing
emergency food to ease the

43:36.900 --> 43:38.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
crisis in the short-term.

43:38.933 --> 43:41.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Jeremiah Kibanya coordinates
relief efforts for World Vision.

43:41.900 --> 43:46.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEREMIAH KIBANYA, World
Vision: We are providing
food commodities to the
people who right now

43:47.933 --> 43:50.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not having anything to eat.

43:50.033 --> 43:54.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We will need money to help
people get more animals into
their family and begin their

43:56.033 --> 43:58.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
livelihood.

43:58.100 --> 44:00.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: How
much do you need, and what
percentage are you getting?

44:00.266 --> 44:04.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEREMIAH KIBANYA: World Vision
has requested for about $37
million be able to respond.

44:04.566 --> 44:07.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And, so far, we have
received $11 million.

44:07.866 --> 44:12.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Most of
that money, $10 million, has
come from the U.S. government.

44:14.933 --> 44:19.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Seattle-based agency is
helping deliver medical care
for those most vulnerable to

44:19.200 --> 44:22.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
drought: pregnant
women and children.

44:22.300 --> 44:25.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At this clinic in the
village of Gabiley, babies
are measured and weighed.

44:25.900 --> 44:30.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
A simple test with an
armband determines their
level of nutrition.

44:30.033 --> 44:33.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Yellow means moderate
malnutrition.

44:33.233 --> 44:35.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Red means severe.

44:35.266 --> 44:39.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If there's malnourishment,
the mothers are given packets
of peanut paste, along with

44:39.266 --> 44:44.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
guidance to administer it only
to the sickest children, says
clinic director Asha Abdi Ali.

44:46.166 --> 44:50.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's very difficult for a
mother if she has other children
who are hungry to not share

44:50.066 --> 44:51.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
it?

44:51.766 --> 44:53.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
ASHA ABDI ALI, Clinic
Director: We tell them
for the same reason.

44:53.233 --> 44:54.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's that these other
children are not in need.

44:54.800 --> 44:56.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It is only for this child.

44:56.800 --> 44:59.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: But
it's still difficult?

44:59.433 --> 45:01.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ASHA ABDI ALI: It's
still difficult.

45:01.500 --> 45:05.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Keeping
people healthy is now made even
more difficult, ironically,

45:05.933 --> 45:08.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by rain.

45:08.033 --> 45:12.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Some rains have arrived this
year, and that's been enough
to green up the landscape.

45:14.100 --> 45:16.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the effects of the
drought are going to linger
for a much longer time.

45:16.100 --> 45:20.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, more immediately,
the threat to public
health is even greater.

45:20.100 --> 45:24.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
That's because there are
millions of livestock
carcasses strewn all
over the landscape, and

45:24.966 --> 45:29.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what the rains do is
wash contaminants into
sources of drinking water.

45:29.966 --> 45:34.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On a hillside just outside
Dilla, a village about
an hour's drive from
the capital, carcasses

45:36.700 --> 45:39.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
have become an unmanageable
problem for Mayor
Ibrahim Abdi Haji.

45:39.100 --> 45:42.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IBRAHIM ABDI HAJI, Mayor of
Dilla (through translator):
It is a bigger problem than we

45:42.600 --> 45:44.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
can handle alone.

45:44.133 --> 45:46.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We have asked the government for
help to burn those dead animals.

45:46.800 --> 45:48.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But we haven't
received help yet.

45:48.833 --> 45:51.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're afraid the community
will get waterborne
diseases from the animals.

45:51.433 --> 45:53.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
We are very scared.

45:53.466 --> 45:57.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Water
which has collected at a nearby
earthen dam, has been completely

45:57.633 --> 46:00.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
contaminated by both dead
and diseased animals.

46:00.600 --> 46:05.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEREMIAH KIBANYA: And if people
use that water because of
desperation, and they don't have

46:05.066 --> 46:10.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
any other water to drink, that
poses another threat again to
outbreak of waterborne diseases

46:11.600 --> 46:13.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to the communities.

46:13.666 --> 46:18.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That can lead to outbreaks
of diseases like acute
water diarrhea or cholera.

46:20.433 --> 46:23.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN: I want to show you
the best way of making
your water clean and safe.

46:23.766 --> 46:28.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: As a
short-term solution, World
Vision has distributed
some 75,000 filters

46:30.133 --> 46:32.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and chlorine tablets, so
people can purify their water.

46:32.966 --> 46:37.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But World Vision's
Kibanya says the other
issues, food shortages,
limited medical services

46:39.133 --> 46:41.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and lack of jobs, are
tougher ones to tackle.

46:41.400 --> 46:46.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
There's a tradition
in this region, where
droughts are localized,
that communities welcome

46:46.233 --> 46:49.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people temporarily displaced
by the dry conditions.

46:49.533 --> 46:54.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But one of Dilla's newcomers,
Roda Yusaf, a mother of seven,
isn't sure she can return

46:55.600 --> 46:57.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to her former livelihood
without animals.

46:57.966 --> 47:00.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
She plans to stay in
Dilla indefinitely.

47:00.133 --> 47:05.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RODA YUSAF, Somaliland (through
translator): When you come from
another area, it's difficult

47:05.800 --> 47:07.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to get a job here.

47:07.066 --> 47:09.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But the community has
been very supportive.

47:09.166 --> 47:13.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: Six years
ago, Dilla was in a similar
position of hosting displaced

47:13.733 --> 47:18.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
persons from a severe famine
which ended up killing
260,000 people in Somalia.

47:20.333 --> 47:23.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Mayor Haji hopes that
doesn't happen again.

47:23.866 --> 47:28.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It seems to be a tradition
here for sharing and helping
people who are in distress in

47:29.466 --> 47:30.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the tribe.

47:30.833 --> 47:32.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
After some time, does
that become difficult?

47:32.800 --> 47:37.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
IBRAHIM ABDI HAJI (through
translator): We are starting
to reach that point.

47:40.033 --> 47:42.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The last time we supported
displaced people who
had come here, everybody
ended up suffering.

47:42.000 --> 47:46.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: The repeated
cycles of drought over the
past 25 years is constantly

47:47.933 --> 47:50.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on the minds of aid workers
and political leaders.

47:50.166 --> 47:53.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Saad Ali Shire is
Somaliland's foreign minister.

47:53.466 --> 47:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAAD ALI SHIRE, Somaliland
Foreign Minister: We need to
look into the future and build

47:57.600 --> 48:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
resilience, so when the drought
comes next time -- and it
will come, because these are

48:04.233 --> 48:06.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
now more severe and
more frequent, because
of the climate change.

48:06.733 --> 48:11.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: He
says much greater long-term
investment must be made
to improve the region's

48:12.166 --> 48:14.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
viability.

48:14.266 --> 48:18.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAAD ALI SHIRE: We need
to change the way we raise
livestock in this country.

48:19.800 --> 48:24.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We very much follow --
we raise livestock as we
raised it 200 years ago.

48:25.200 --> 48:27.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a nomadic way.

48:27.366 --> 48:31.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think we need to settle
and grow food for livestock.

48:31.466 --> 48:36.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we also need, I think, to
orient part of our population
towards fishing and other

48:40.133 --> 48:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
activities, industry, services.

48:42.566 --> 48:46.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
FRED DE SAM LAZARO: However,
that seems unlikely,
at least in the short
term, given that urgent

48:48.566 --> 48:52.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
appeals to deal with the
immediate needs have fallen far
short of what the U.N. and aid

48:53.600 --> 48:55.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
agencies have requested.

48:55.666 --> 49:00.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Fred de Sam Lazaro reporting
from Dilla, Somaliland.

